criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with intestinal ischemia and acute abdomen pain caused by superior mesenteric
             artery thromboembolism

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Intestinal ischemia patients who have been infected with toxic shock and unstable
             circulation;

          -  Those who have acute large-area myocardial infarction, large-area cerebral infarction,
             or have serious heart failure or sequelae of cerebral infarction within 1 month;

          -  Combined with portal hypertension, gastrointestinal hemorrhage, portal and mesenteric
             venous reflux obstruction diseases;

          -  Contrast agent allergy, severe renal insufficiency, and inability to perform
             intravascular surgery;

          -  Patients with severe cardiopulmonary disease, uncontrollable hypertension and other
             poor surgical tolerance;

          -  Patients with advanced malignant tumors with intestinal obstruction or life expectancy
             <2 years.
